We proved that light from microscopic bubbles that were excited using ultrasound energy could be harnessed for real practical use, even at high (body) temperature.
We also demonstrated that light could be used to trap and control microscopic bubble ensembles.
We also developed a new and enhanced means of imaging in the sub microsecond framing regime.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>patents arising have been generated and may be licensed to Cordin. Discussions to that end have already occurred with CTO Cordin.
